{
  "text": "Example 4.10. Let C \u2282 Z be the germ of a surface along a curve C \u223c = P 1 such that the singular locus of Z is a point Q such that (Q \u2208 Z) \u223c = (x 2 + y 4 + yz 3 = 0)/Z 2 (1, 1, 1). In this example we will construct a divisorial extremal neighborhood f : C \u2282 Y \u2212\u2192 X \u2283 P such that the general section of |O Y | is Z, the general member of |O X | is Duval of type D 4 and the general member of | \u2212 K Y | is DuVal of type E 7 if n = 3, or D 4 if n = 2. Hence if \u0393 is the center of the f -exceptional divisor, then the general hyperplane section of X containing \u0393 is DuVal of type D 4 if n = 2 or of type E 7 if n = 3. Let f : Z \u2212\u2192 H be the contraction of C to a DuVal singularity of type D 4 . Let Q \u2208 Y be the smoothing of Q \u2208 Z given by (x 2 + y 4 + yz 3 + t n = 0)/Z 2 (1, 1, 1, 0) where n \u2208 {2, 3}. Let \u03c0 : Y \u2032 \u2212\u2192 Y be the index 1 cover of Y . This is given by x 2 + y 4 + yz 3 + t n = 0. Let S \u2032 be the section given by z = 0. This is in the same eigenspace as \u2212K \u2032 Y and hence S = S \u2032 /Z 2 (1, 1, 0) belongs to | \u2212 K Y |. I claim that S is DuVal of type D 4 if n = 2, or E 7 if n = 3. Indeed. S \u2032 is given by x 2 + t n + y 4 = 0. This is an A 3 singularity if n = 2 and E 6 if n = 3. Now setting u = x 2 , v = y 2 and xy = w it follows that S is given by w 2 \u2212 uv = u + v 2 + t n = 0. Hence S is given by w 2 \u2212 vt n \u2212 v 3 = 0 and therefore it is of type D 4 if n = 2 and E 7 if n = 3. In any case, Q \u2208 Y is terminal [CITATION_1] . Let Def(Z) \u2212\u2192 Def(Q \u2208 Z) be the natural map. It is known that it is smooth and in particular surjective [Ko-Mo92]. Therefore the local deformation Q \u2208 Y of Q \u2208 Z lifts to a global deformation Y of Z. Moreover, since K Y is S 2 , P \u2208 S lifts to a section S \u2208 | \u2212 K Y |. Let f : Y \u2212\u2192 X be the extension of f : Z \u2212\u2192 H to Y . Then this is a divisorial extremal neighborhood such that Z is the general member of |O Y |. Let E be the f -exceptional divisor and \u0393 its center in X. Then by construction, if n = 2 then both the general hyperplane section of X and the general through \u0393 are DuVal of type D 4 . On the other hand, if n = 3, then the general hyperplane section of X is D 4 and the general section containing \u0393 is E 7 .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "116194977"
  },
  "bib_entries": {
    "116194977": {
      "title": "Young person's guide to canonical singularities",
      "abstract": "A copier of the type which includes a photoreceptor on which an electrostatic latent image may be formed, a movable applicator which carries developer from a working supply of image developer and applies it to the image, and developer dispensing instrumentalities for replenishing the working supply of developer, is provided with a system for controlling the developer dispensing instrumentalities and thus replenishment of the working supply of developer. The control system responds to the optical density of developer on the applicator to generate a signal indicating whether or not the working supply of developer is in need of replenishment, and this signal is utilized for energizing the dispensing instrumentalities. The control system also includes circuitry for preventing energization of the dispensing instrumentalities for a predetermined time interval after commencement of movement of the applicator, to be sure that the applicator has picked up a sample of the developer from the working supply. Preferably, the control system further includes circuitry for replenishing the working supply of developer for at least a predetermined minimum time interval after replenishment is commenced."
    }
  }
